chapter.sect1:
Upgrading &productname;
The supported upgrade method is to install all upgrades, in order. Skipping releases is not supported. This table matches the Helm chart versions to each release:
&releases-table;
Use helm list to see the version of your installed release . Verify the latest release is the next sequential release from your installed release. If it is, proceed with the commands below to perform the upgrade.
The following procedure will upgrade &productname; 2.0 to &productname; &productnumber;.
Begin by upgrading &operator;.
&prompt.user;helm upgrade cf-operator suse/cf-operator \ --namespace cf-operator \ --set "global.operator.watchNamespace=kubecf" \ --version &operator_chart;
Wait until &operator; is successfully upgraded before proceeding. Monitor the status of your &operator; upgrade using the watch command.
&prompt.user;watch --color 'kubectl get pods --namespace cf-operator'
When the &operator; upgrade is completed, upgrade &kubecf;.
&prompt.user;helm upgrade kubecf suse/kubecf \ --namespace kubecf \ --values &values-file; \ --version &kubecf_chart;
Monitor the status of your &kubecf; upgrade using the watch command.
&prompt.user;watch --color 'kubectl get pods --namespace kubecf'
